==English==

===Etymology===
'''Niall''' is a forename of [[Gaelic]] - [[Ireland|Irish]] or [[Scotland|Scottish]] - origin. Its original meaning is obscure, but ''Champion'' is the most popular meaning assigned to it today. 

The name '''Neil''' is a corruption of the name [[Niall]]. '''Neil''' derives perhaps from the [[vocative]] form of the Gaelic name, which is Nèill. The name comes into French and Norman-Latin as '''Nigell-us''', originally pronounced almost identically. The name, like many Gaelic names, is borrowed into [[Old Norse|Norse]] as  Njál.

Other anglicized forms of the name are Neal, Niel, Neale, Neall.

